                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n                              <p>with worldly substance have been largely called on for the<lb/>\n                                        <add>?</add> of their own as well as the <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">General</hi> poor of the City.\n                                        Large<lb/> Collections have been made both in the Synagogue\n                                        as well as out<lb/> of doors. Notwithstanding, the great\n                                        mass of our people are materially<lb/> altered in\n                                        circumstances, so much so, that I fear the pecuniary<lb/>\n                                        position of our synagogues will be much affected\n                                        thereby.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">A Day of General Humiliation was appointed<lb/>\n                                        and observed on <date>Friday the 1<hi rend=\"sup\">st</hi>\n                                                  Nov.</date> last, but owing to the<lb/> inclemency\n                                        of the weather which prevented a great majority from<lb/>\n                                        attending, the Governor appointed <date>Wednesday the 13<hi\n                                                  rend=\"sup\">th</hi></date> following for a<lb/>\n                                        similar purpose. I need scarcely add lost days were\n                                        religiously<lb/> observed by our people.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">There seems to be a desire manifested in<lb/>\n                                        <placeName>Falmouth</placeName> for the establishment of a\n                                        regular congregation, and the erection<lb/> of a synagogue,\n                                        but I fear, that internal dissensions, chiefly relative<lb/>\n                                        to <add>מנהג</add> are obstanly<add>?</add> to so desirable\n                                        an end. Perhaps a few<lb/> remarks from your pen in the\n                                        Occident might be serviceable.</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I forgot to state that a “Hebrew Benevolent<lb/>\n                                        Society” has been formed for the relief of our destitute\n                                        Brethren<lb/> during the prevalence of the Cholera. It is to\n                                        be hoped that when the<lb/> Almighty shall have, in His\n                                        mercy, removed from us this “noisome<lb/> pestilence,” the\n                                        association will not be suffered to fall to the ground.</p>\n                              "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3v698z41/canvas/p2"
                }
